{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2014}} {{Use Australian English|date=December 2014}} {{Infobox recurring event | name = Art, Not Apart | native_name = | logo = [[File:Art, Not Apart logo.png]] | logo_caption = | image = | imagesize = frameless | caption = | date = | begins = | ends = | frequency = Annually | location = [[Canberra]] | first = 2011 | last = | participants = | genre = Contemporary Arts Festival | patron = | website = http://artnotapart.com/ | footnotes = }} '''Art, Not Apart''' is an annual [[Australian]] contemporary arts festival held in [[Canberra]], providing an opportunity for artists to display their works and connect with the community.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/art-not-apart-festival-once-a-year-and-its-a-big-day-art-20140314-34ssq.html |newspaper=The Canberra Times |publisher=Fairfax Media |title=Art, Not Apart festival: Once a year, and it's a big day art |first=Natasha |last=Rudra|date=15 March 2014 |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141215090241/http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/art-not-apart-festival-once-a-year-and-its-a-big-day-art-20140314-34ssq.html |archivedate=15 December 2014}}</ref><ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/footloose-and-fancyfree-at-the-art-fair-20121027-28d08.html |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20121029143249/http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/footloose-and-fancyfree-at-the-art-fair-20121027-28d08.html |archivedate=29 October 2012 |first=Christopher |last=Knaus |newspaper=The Canberra Times |publisher=Fairfax Media |date=28 October 2012 |title=Footlose and fancy-free at the art fair }}</ref>
The Art, Not Apart festival features exhibitions, performance art, numerous music stages, installations, strange interventions, street food, cafes and a dance party.<ref>{{Cite web|url=http://artnotapart.com/philosophy|title=About {{!}} Art, Not Apart|website=artnotapart.com|language=en|access-date=2017-09-07}}</ref> The festival producer, David Caffery, told media that in producing Art Not Apart, he is consciously trying not to copy other events.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/canberra-life/canberras-most-significant-art-festival-art-not-apart-takes-over-new-acton-westside-20150312-142apq.html|title=Canberra's 'most significant' art festival Art, Not Apart takes over New Acton, Westside|first=Clare|last=Colley|date=13 March 2015|newspaper=The Canberra Times|publisher=Fairfax Media|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160302103546/http://www.canberratimes.com.au/act-news/canberra-life/canberras-most-significant-art-festival-art-not-apart-takes-over-new-acton-westside-20150312-142apq.html|archivedate=2 March 2016}}</ref>
The first Art, Not Apart was held in New Acton in 2011.<ref>{{cite news |url= http://www.canberratimes.com.au/entertainment/art-and-design/art-not-apart-20140218-32xsy.html |newspaper=The Canberra Times |publisher=Fairfax Media |date=24 February 2014 |first=Emma |last=Kelly |archiveurl= https://web.archive.org/web/20141219225551/http://www.canberratimes.com.au/entertainment/art-and-design/art-not-apart-20140218-32xsy.html |archivedate=19 December 2014 |title=Art, Not Apart}}</ref> Since the construction of the pop-up Westside shipping container precinct in 2015, the festival grew to include Westside Acton Park in 2015 and 2016.<ref>{{cite news|url=http://www.smh.com.au/comment/art-not-apart-festival-time-for-canberra-to-become-a-design-leader-20150316-1m0c8l.html|newspaper=The Sydney Morning Herald|publisher=Fairfax Media|date=20 March 2015|title=Art, Not Apart festival: Time for Canberra to become a design leader|first=Chris|last=Wallace|archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20160307082558/http://www.smh.com.au/comment/art-not-apart-festival-time-for-canberra-to-become-a-design-leader-20150316-1m0c8l.html|archivedate=7 March 2016}}</ref>
